body:
I'm developing a .NET Core APP and want to deploy it on CentOS 7. I'm using SkiaSharp to generate a captcha code. 

Here is my references:

```XML
<PackageReference Include="Avalonia.Skia.Linux.Natives" Version="1.57.1.4" />
<PackageReference Include="SkiaSharp" Version="1.57.1" />
```

Here is my code:
```CSharp
        private Task ProcessCaptcha(HttpContext context)
        {
            // CREATING THE DRAWING SURFACE

            // constract the information describing the desired surface
            var info = new SKImageInfo(100, 20);
            // create the surface using the information
            var surface = SKSurface.Create(info);


            // CLEARING THE SURFACE

            // get the canvas that we can draw on
            var canvas = surface.Canvas;
            // clear the canvas / view
            canvas.Clear(SKColors.Red);


            // DRAWING TEXT

            // create the paint for the text
            var textPaint = new SKPaint
            {
                IsAntialias = true,
                Style = SKPaintStyle.Fill,                
                Color = SKColors.White,
                TextSize = 24
            };
            // draw the text (from the baseline)
            canvas.DrawText("SkiaSharp", 0, 18, textPaint);            

            // ENCODING THE SURFACE

            // create a raster instance of the surface
            var image = surface.Snapshot();

            var data = image.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);

            data.SaveTo(context.Response.Body);

            return Task.FromResult<object>(null);
        }
```

When I run it on CentOS 7, I can only see an image with red background. Is there anything I've missed?
